{"title_page": "Reina Hispanoamericana 2019", "text_new": "{{Short description|Bolivian beauty pageant}}\n{{Infobox beauty pageant\n| caption = Reina Hispanoamericana 2019\n| date = February 8, 2020\n| venue = [[Santa Cruz de la Sierra|Santa Cruz]], [[Bolivia]]\n| number of contestants =\n| presenters = \n| acts =\n| entrants = 29\n| placements = 11\n| broadcaster =\n| debuts =\n| withdraws = [[Canada]]\n| returns =  \n| winner =  '''{{flag|Mexico}}''' \u2013 Regina Peredo\n|-\n| congeniality =   '''{{flag|United States}}''' \u2013 Monserrat B\u00e1ez\n| photogenic = '''{{flag|Puerto Rico}}''' \u2013 Yuanile Alvarado\n| best national costume = '''{{flag|Guatemala}}''' Stefani Zece\u00f1a\n| before = [[Reina Hispanoamericana 2018|2018]]\n| next = Reina Hispanoamericana 2020\n}}\n\n'''Reina Hispanoamericana 2019''' was the 29th edition of the Reina Hispanoamericana pageant. It was held on February 8, 2020 in [[Santa Cruz de la Sierra|Santa Cruz]], [[Bolivia]]. At the end of that event, Nariman Battikah of Venezuela crowned Regina Peredo of [[M\u00e9xico]] has her successor.\n\n== Final Results ==\n{| class=\"wikitable unsortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! Final results\n! Contestant\n|-\n| '''Reina Hispanoamericana 2019'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Mexico}}''' \u2013 '''Regina Peredo'''\n|-\n| '''Virreina Hispanoamericana 2019'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Brasil}}''' \u2013 Gabrielle Vilela de Souza\n|-\n| '''1st runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Colombia}}''' \u2013 Laura Claro\n|-\n| '''2nd runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Puerto Rico}}''' -Yuanilie Alvarado\n|-\n| '''3rd runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Paraguay}}''' \u2013 Ketlin Lottermann\n|-\n| '''4th runner-up'''\n|\n*'''{{flag|Venezuela}}''' \u2013 Valeria Badell\n|-\n| '''5th runner-up'''\t\n|\n*'''{{flag|Philippines}}''' \u2013 Katrina Llegado '''\u0394''' \n|-\n| '''6th runner-up'''\n|\n*'''{{flag|Spain}}''' - Ainara Carda\u00f1o\n|-\n| '''7th runner-up'''\n|\n*'''{{flag|Dominican Republic}}''' \u2013 Franchesca Astier\n|-\n| '''8