t. Nivas K Prasanna |date=20 June 2017 |language=Tamil |publisher=[[Think Music India]] |place=India |access-date=24 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724083230/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oE6zm6OAghg |archive-date=24 July 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Short films ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n!Role(s)\n!Director\n! Language\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|{{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Herova? Zerova?]]'' \n|Himself\n|[[V. Priya]]|| Tamil || <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |title=TN actors in documentary highlighting evils of child labour |date=16 May 2008 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=10 February 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604120118/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200805162223.htm |archive-date=4 June 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of awards and nominations received by Suriya]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|name=Suriya filmography|id=1421814}}\n\n{{featured list}}\n\n[[Category:Actor filmographies]]\n[[Category:Indian filmographies]]\n", "name_user": "Shamnu Sfc", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eAs an actor)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suriya_filmography"}
{"title_page": "Sharif Aghayar", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{short description|Azerbaijani writer}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| embed            = \n| honorific_prefix = \n| name             = Sharif Aghayar\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = \u015e\u0259rif Ziyadxan o\u011flu A\u011fayarov.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| image_upright    = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| pseudonym        = \n| birth_name       = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1976|01|01}} \n| birth_place      = Agbulag, Lachin District, [[Azerbaijan Soviet Socialist Republic]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| death_date       =  \n| death_place      = \n| resting_place    = \n| occupation       = \n| language         = [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]]\n| residence        = \n| nationality      = [[Azerbaijan]]\n| citizenship      = \n| education        = [[Azerbaijan State Pedagogical University]]\n| alma_mater       = \n| home_town        = \n| period           = \n| genre            = <!-- or: | genres = -->\n| subject          = <!-- or: | subjects = -->\n| movement         = \n| notableworks     = <!-- or: | notablework = -->\n| spouse           = <!-- or: | spouses = -->\n| partner          = <!-- or: | partners = -->\n| children         = \n| relatives        = \n| awards           = \n| signature        = \n| signature_alt    = \n| years_active     = \n| module           = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.org}} -->\n| portaldisp       = <!-- \"on\", \"yes\", \"true\", etc.; or omit -->\n}}\n'''Sharif Aghayar''' (full name: ''Sharif Ziyadkhan Aghayarov''; January 1, 1976, Agbulag, Lachin district), Azerbaijani writer.\n\n== Life ==\nSharif Aghayar was born on January 1, 1976, in the village of Agbulag of Lachin District.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\">{{cite web|url=https://edebiyyat-az.com/?p=4626 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306121608/https://edebiyyat-az.com/?p=4626 |archivedate=2020-03-06 |title=\u015e\u0259rif A\u011eAYAR.H\u0259yat\u0131 v\u0259 Yarad\u0131c\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131 |author= |date=2013-08-27 |work= |publisher=edebiyyat-az.com |accessdate=2015-06-12 |language=az}}</ref>\nIn 1980-1991, he studied at the secondary school in the village of Agbulag. In 1992, he was admitted to the Faculty of History and Philology at the Shusha branch of the Azerbaijan State Pedagogical University named after N. Tusi. For a time he worked as a teacher at Aghdam Agricultural Technical School in Agjabadi. He came to Baku in 1998 and began working as a reporter in the cultural department of \u201cPanorama\u201d newspaper.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\n== Awards ==\nHe was awarded the ''Khalil Rza Ulut\u00fcrk Prize'',<ref name=\"Pozuq foto\u015f\u0259kill\u0259r\"/> created in 1998 by the Writers Union and the Independent Trade Union of Culture Workers, and the Youth Prize in 2003 by the Ministry of Youth and Sports for his achievements in the field of literature. The same year he won first Proza N Internet Competition held by the YeniSI Center for Literary and Art Studies in Azerbaijan.\n\nOn November 23, 2015, he was awarded ''Rafik Mountain Prize'' by the Dalga Youth Organization for his enlightenment and active work.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kulis.az/news/13903 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306122632/https://kulis.az/news/13903 |archivedate=2020-03-06 |title=\u015e\u0259rif A\u011fayara \"Rafiq Ta\u011f\u0131 m\u00fckafat\u0131\" verildi |author= |date= 2015-11-23 |work= |publisher=kulis.lent.az |accessdate=2015-11-23 |language=az}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, he was named ''\"Literary Man of the Year\"'' by the Azerbaijan Creative Fund. The same year, he won the prestigious nomination of the Golden Word Literary Prize established by the Ministry of Culture for his novel \"The City beyond the Dreams.\"\n\n== Activities ==\nIn 2000, he was invited by the \u201cNew Azerbaijan\u201d newspaper to write articles in the field of culture and literature and prepare special editions. He worked for the newspaper until the end of 2003. He has published numerous articles, poems, essays, and stories. On November 20, 2003, he was appointed editor-in-chief of the \u201cKino+\u201d newspaper.\n\nSharif Aghayar represented Azerbaijan at the 3rd Poets Meeting of Turkic-speaking countries and peoples held at the initiative of [[TURKSOY]] in Malatya, Turkey on October 21\u201328, 2002.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\nA book of poems entitled \"Masnavi of Desert\" initiated by the Vector Science Center was published in 2003, and the \"The Brick Man's Saga\" narrative, was ranked in the top ten of the 2010 National Book Award.  The EL Publishing House published his prose book named \u201cAftafali Antact\u201d and in 2011, Qanun Publishing House published his novel \"Haramy\" within \"New Literature\" series.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\nIn 2013, the \"Zero\" Publishing House published \"Poor Photos,\" a book of poems within the \"Pocket Books\" series. \"Mrs. T.\" storybook was published by the Writer Publishing House, and \"Gulustan\" and \"The City beyond the Dreams\" novels by Qanun Publishing House in 2015 and 2016, respectively.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\nFrom 2008 to 2013, he was a consultant in the Department of Publishing, Advertising and Information at the [[Ministry of Culture and Tourism (Azerbaijan)|Ministry of Culture and Tourism]]. Currently, he works as the chief editor at the \u201cKulis.az\u201d literature portal.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\n== Works ==\nHis folk and epic poems (\"Prayer\", \"May 92\", \"Chamber\", \"Brother\", \"Unpainted Mizrab Nails\", \"Civilization\", \"Mystery of the Wind\", \"Cat Anzar\", \"Modern Poems\" \"etc.) caused great interest of readers and critics, and dozens of articles were published in their regard.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\nAt the same time, \"Dagal\", \"Dima's notes\", \"Our house\", \"Balabey\", \"Georgy's house\", \"Anakhanum\u201d, \"First day without Lachin\", \"It seemed like a funny story\", \"Military-political issue.\", \"Shuglov Method\", \"Picture\", \"Gumru\", \"Babash\" stories,\" \u201cThe Brick Man's Saga\" and \"Hurrem\" narratives,\" \u201cHarami\", \"Gulustan\", \"The City beyond the Dreams\", \"White Lake\" and \"Commander\" novels have earned him a special place among writers of the next generation.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\n[[Alaviyya Babayeva]], [[Elchin Afandiyev]], [[Vagif Yusifli]], [[Rashad Majid]], [[Adil Mirseyid]], [[Mahir Garayev]], [[Asad Jahangir (writer)|Asad Jahangir]], [[Javanshir Yusifli]], [[Tehran Alishanoglu]], [[Tofig Abdin]], [[Akif Ali]], [[Vurgun Ayyub]], [[Elnara Akimova]], [[Irada Musatayeva Haji]], [[Jalil Javanshir]], [[Aikhan Ayvaz]] and other well-known writers wrote interesting articles about his works.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\nHis writings and works have been published on kulis.az, qafqazinfo.az, qaynar.info, oxuzali.az and other web-sites with stories placed in electronic libraries.<ref name=\"H\u0259yat\u0131\"/>\n\n=== Books ===\n# \"Masnavi of Desert\" (Poems), Baku, \"Vector\" Publishing House, 2003\t\n# \"The Brick Man's Saga\" (narrative), Qanun Publishing House, 2010\n# \"Aftafali Antract\" (Baku), Baku, \"EL\" Publishing House, 2010\n# \"Harami\" (Baku), Baku, Qanun Publishing House, 2011\n# \"Poor photos\" (poems), Baku, \"Zero\" Publishing House, 2013. 88 p.<ref name=\"Pozuq foto\u015f\u0259kill\u0259r\">{{cite web|url=https://edebiyyat-az.com/?p=4717 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306122154/https://edebiyyat-az.com/?p=4717 |archivedate=2020-03-06 |title=\u015e\u0259rif A\u011fayar\u0131n \"Pozuq foto\u015f\u0259kill\u0259r\" kitab\u0131 i\u015f\u0131q \u00fcz\u00fc g\u00f6rd\u00fc |author= |date= 2013-08-28 |work= |publisher=edebiyyat-az.com |accessdate=2015-06-12 |language=az}}</ref>\n# \"Mrs. T.\" (storybook), Baku, \"Writer\" Publishing House, 2013. 174 p.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edebiyyat-az.com/?p=4712 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306123144/https://edebiyyat-az.com/?p=4712 |archivedate=2020-03-06 |title=\u015e\u0259rif A\u011fayar\u0131n \"Xan\u0131m T.\" kitab\u0131 i\u015f\u0131q \u00fcz\u00fc g\u00f6rd\u00fc |author= |date= 2013-08-28 |work= |publisher=edebiyyat-az.com |accessdate=2015-06-12 |language=az}}</ref>\n# \"Gulustan\" (novel), Baku, Qanun Publishing House, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kulis.az/news/13845 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306123427/https://kulis.az/news/13845 |archivedate=2020-03-06 |title=\u015e\u0259rif A\u011fayar\u0131n roman\u0131 \u00e7ap olundu |author= |date= 2015-11-16 |work= |publisher=kulis.lent.az |accessdate=2015-11-17 |language=az}}</ref>\n# \"The City beyond the Dreams\" (Novel), Baku, Qanun Publishing House, 2017\n# White Lake (novel), Baku, Qanun Publishing House, 2018\n\n=== Stories ===\n* ''Sharif Aghayar'', \"Shuglov Method\" - libliq.org\n* ''Sharif Aghayar'', Military-Political Issues - News.lent.az\n\n=== Narratives ===\n* ''Sharif Aghayar'', \"The Brick Man's Saga\" (Povest) - Liberty.org\n\n=== Essays ===\n* ''Sharif Aghayar'', \"God has chosen the book\" - kulis.lent.az\n\n=== Articles ===\n* ''Sharif Aghayar'', \"Our Lyrical People\" (Article). - edebiyyat-az.com\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aghayar, Sharif}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan State Pedagogical University alumni]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani poets]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Azerbaijani writer}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| embed            = \n| honorific_prefix = \n| name             = Sharif Aghayar\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = \u015e\u0259rif Ziyadxan o\u011flu A\u011fayarov.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| image_upright    = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| pseudonym